Although not a common caliber, ammo for this gun is readily available at most major retailers including Walmart.  Perfect for a smaller hand, the grip is the same dimensions as it's 9mm cousin - but with 45acp power.  45GAP (Glock Action Pistol) was a proprietary invention of Glock to address the fact that widebody Glock 45's weren't easy to grip for smaller hands.  Ballistically almost identical to 45ACP.  With the extra barrel length and weight the recoil on this pistol is very mild.  Perfect for the first home defense weapon.  Price is firm, 100 bucks worth of ammo and four mags.

title: For Sale/Trade:  ***SOLD***  Remington 870 SPS Shurshot Synthetic Super Slug
postcontent:
This is an incredible shotgun with no more than 20 slugs fired through it and is in perfect cosmetic condition. Comes with Redfield scope and hard case. I am only selling this because I can no longer deer hunt due to a health condition.

From Remington's site:

The most dependable slide action of all time in three advanced designs that will go the distance with deadly precision, whether your target is the crease behind a bucks shoulder or a big red head. Weve built the industrys finest rifled slug guns for years, but our new 12-gauge Model 870 SPS ShurShot Synthetic Super Slug advances deer-leveling technology to farther reaches and smaller group sizes than ever before possible. Even more so when paired with high-performance ammunition like our Premier AccuTip sabot slugs.

Because barrel stability is key to extended-range accuracy, this shotguns barrel is of extra-heavy, 1" diameter configuration and measures a full 25 1/2". Its also pinned to the receiver to control vibration for rifle-like, shot-to-shot consistency. Five longitudinal flutes keep weight and heat buildup to a minimum while bolstering barrel rigidity. Six Parabolic Ultragon rifling grooves with a 1-in-35" twist optimize slug flight. But much more than just the ultimate accuracy-enhancing barrel design, this shotgun provides the rock-steady aim and outstanding pointability of our ambidextrous ShurShot pistol-grip synthetic stock. Rubberized overmolding at the pistol grip and extended fore-end offer a sure hold in adverse conditions. For unmatched shooting comfort, we added the SuperCell recoil pad. The receiver is drilled and tapped, and the included Weaver rail makes adding optics a cinch. Sling swivel studs are built in.


Key Features:

    25 1/2" extra-heavy, 1"-diameter barrel with longitudinal flutes for reduced weight
    Barrel is pinned to the receiver for the utmost in shot-to-shot stability
    Parabolic Ultragon rifling with a 1:35" twist
    Built on the famous Model 870 action

    ShurShot pistol-grip stock and fore-end with rubberized overmolding at grip areas
    SuperCell recoil pad

title: For Sale:  1917 Eddystone 30-06 military gun w/ scope Great Condition! Good Christmas present.
postcontent:
The stock shows some wear but can be refinished easily.  Bussell scope. I have pics to email or I will post them later. 

Some history on this gun.  

The 1917 enfield was originally designed for the british as the pattern 1914 or P-14 enfield ,,it was chambered for the 303 british cartridge and was produced by winchester +remington ,,The British were in the midst of ww1 and were haveing trouble produceing enough No1mkIII rifles and asked for help from the US ,,the US companys steped up to the plate and designed a rifle cheaper to mass produce than the enfield and the p-14 was designed ,,there were many sent to Britan during ww1 but the British troops liked the no1 over the p-14 and so the p-14 was used as secondary reserve rifles ,,Later on in the war the US entered the conflict and production of the 1903 springfield was in full swing and rifles couldn't be produced fast enough to satisfy the demand ,, The companys that built the p-14 deceided that they could retool and chamber the rifle to the new 30-06 round,, and the 1917 or p17 enfield was born,,the p-14 and P17 were so simular that during ww2 over a million P17's were sent to Britan on the lend lease program and these 30-06 rifle had to have a red stripe painted on the stock to distinguish them from the 303 chambered p14 rifles ,,the rifles never saw the action the 1903 Springfield saw and alot of soilders complaind that they were heavy and akward and favored the 1903 rifles over the 1917,,so again the 1917 was used mostly with home defence and training purposes,,during ww2 it was also used as home defence and training and again saw limited action mostly in the Pacific,, 

,,The action on the 1917 is a very robust action based on the Mauser dual locking lug design and have been the starting point for many fine custom sporting rifles because of the strenght of the action and the long magazine lenght allowing for rechambering in calibers as large as the 458 mag with only minor modifications to the magazine ,, this rifle was also the father to Remingtons model 30 bolt action which was Remingtons first high power sporting rifle and it used a modified 1917 action design and even had the bent bolt simular to the 1917,,,The actions from these rifles can sell for around 250 alone to gunsmiths for custom rifle building ,,complete unaltered rifle can sell in the 400-650 range for the most manufactures and even higher for Winchester examples if complete and original,,the Eddystone models were actually made by Remington at there Eddystone Pa. plant,,your winchester might be better answered by our moderator 2bit,,
bigcurt

title: For Sale/Trade:  HK91 - greek made
postcontent: Imported by Springfield Armory, this is an HK91 built on german equipment in Greece.  This is NOT a parts gun, this is NOT a Cetme POC, this is NOT a P91 this is the real deal.    For those who dont know, the original SAR8's were actually made in Greece on HK licensed equipment, this is an "overstamp" gun in case you care and know what it means.  Then George Bush the first decided to create the "sporting arms test" and they couldn't import it anymore.  It's as HK as you can get.  This one has a factory bipod and carry handle and I installed an XS sight systems tritium sight set on it (front and rear).  There's a little clamp on picatinny rail that will NOT come with it, but I will inlude an ARMS clamp on rail (picatinny) if you wish to attach a scope to it.  Original german leather sling and the buttstock is a rare variant also.  I have 6 aluminum mags and ten Thermold mags that will come with it. I've put maybe 400 rounds through it. Zombies are impressed by this rifle.   Thiis not even remotely comparable to the later models of SAR sporters that Springfield tried to sell people, it's a Greek manufactured HK91.  Please refrain from offering me your military surplus trash in exchange for this gun, I know who you are and I'm not interested in enriching some collector.  This is a serious rifle for someone who NEEDS it.  Why am I selling it?  I prefer FAL's.  I also have a bit of extra parts that go with this rifle, since I don't have any other HK91's I have a parts kit that includes everything except the receiver (of course) and the green slimline furniture.  Several magazines with it, both aluminum and thermold.  The buyer will also have the right to purchase up to 1k in german ball ammo in 200rd battlepacks at current market rates.

postcontent: Bushmaster has reworked their magazines to offer significant improvements in function, durability and value. The aluminum box is stamped with a full "progressive" die to produce tightest tolerances. The welding process along the box seams has been automated to insure optimum weld ingot, strength and compliance with MIL-STD. The surface finish has been improved to meet or exceed MIL-PRF-46010 (required for U.S.G.I. magazines). Magazine boxes are treated with Molybdenum Disulphide ("Moly") for its exceptional adherence properties which ensure long lasting protection and lubricity - far superior to the PTFE (Teflon) used on other magazines. Finally, these magazines now have a new "anti-tilt" follower that ensures the round is fed into the chamber properly -preventing failure to feed problems. Drop tests have proven the advantages of the anti-tilt follower over the traditional green follower. As an additional aid, the followers are caliber marked - 5.56in this case. Highest quality tempered steel springs, and Bushmaster logo stamped baseplates (removable for cleaning) round out the improvements on these superior magazines - which have been endorsed by the National Tactical Officers Association.

title: For Trade:  1984, 20" 3' Invader Cabin Cuddy I/O Volvo Pentax
postcontent:
Looking to trade straight for an AR/M4 variant rifle.  I would like to have this done by the end of the week.  A great gift for yourself or your family.  

This is a 1984, 20" 3' Invader Cabin Cuddy with a Inboard/Outboard 225HP Volvo Pentax Engine with only 316 hours. I am the 3rd owner. I know the previous owner (who knew the original owner). I bought this when I was in Parris Island, and I LOVED it. I hate to get rid of it, but I have some new hobbies, and an aggressive training schedule at work so that means I just don't get out on the water as much as I would like. I know that it is a little bit older, but the boat and engine are solid. I used to take this with my family on 60 mile round trip runs when I was in SC with NO problems. 

It seats 6 without using the cabin cuddy, or converting the front seats to bench seats. If you convert the driver seat and the passenger seat to bench seats it seats 8. I bought a new radio and fish finder in 2010 which are included. 
Also included are 
-(3) recreational towing inter tubes 
-Anchor and chain 
-Bumpers 
-More than enough life jackets to support any adult / kid combination you might take out with you ( roughly 7 and 7, with 2 or three tubing life jackets included ). 

The speedometer doesn't work (easy fix, just a broken needle). 

I know it's a slightly older boat than some of the other boats you might see, but this is worth every penny. I have never had a problem with the boat, and until 2010, this boat has never seen everything but fresh water. I have taken it as far as 2 miles off shore with no problems. I have thoroughly washed the boat down every time it was taken out. 

Full disclosure. The trailer could use some work. I have towed the trailer from Ohio to South Carolina, and then to North Carolina. The hydraulic brakes on the trailer need to be rebuilt. There is rust damage on the trailer. It was that way when I bought the boat, I just never got around to fixing it. For short jaunts to your local boat ramp, you will be fine, but if you plan on taking it long distances you will probably want to get the breaks fixed and the trailer checked out. 

I have plenty of pictures that I can email or text you.
